---
// src/pages/index.astro
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout door="home">

  <!-- ── Hero ─────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <div class="page-body">
    <section class="hero" aria-label="Introduction">
      <p class="hero-eyebrow">The Skinny Union Project</p>
      <h1 class="hero-headline">
        No employer pays more than it <em>has to.</em>
      </h1>
      <div class="hero-rule"></div>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Not because they're villains &mdash; because that's what employers do. And unlike the
        &ldquo;full fat&rdquo; union package that spends its leverage on non-pay items, the
        skinny union answers in kind: collective bargaining that puts every ounce of leverage
        on wages and benefits, and nothing else.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>

  <!-- ── Three Doors ───────────────────────────────────── -->
  <div class="page-body">
    <nav class="door-grid" aria-label="Site sections">

      <a href="/press" class="door-card door-card--press">
        <span class="door-tag">The Argument</span>
        <span class="door-sub">"The Missing Story"</span>
        <p class="door-desc">
          The professional labor market has a structural compensation problem that collective
          bargaining theory predicts and empirical evidence confirms. The skinny union is the
          mechanism that solves it. The story hasn't been told yet.
        </p>
        <span class="door-arrow">Enter &rarr;</span>
      </a>

      <a href="/employees" class="door-card door-card--employees">
        <span class="door-tag">Employees</span>
        <span class="door-sub">"Get Paid"</span>
        <p class="door-desc">
          You already know what the market pays for your work &mdash; and that you're not
          getting it. Here's what collective bargaining looks like when the only agenda
          is compensation.
        </p>
        <span class="door-arrow">Enter &rarr;</span>
      </a>

      <a href="/research" class="door-card door-card--research">
        <span class="door-tag">Research</span>
        <span class="door-sub">"Ooh, a White Paper!"</span>
        <p class="door-desc">
          The legal architecture is sound. The labor market analysis is documented. The
          objections are addressed head-on. Everything is already here.
        </p>
        <span class="door-arrow">Enter &rarr;</span>
      </a>

    </nav>
  </div>

</BaseLayout>
